Span.Text: CCIO > Cloud Technology

There are many different descriptions of what Cloud computing is, but a very simple explanation is that it means you can access your systems, data and documents from the Internet rather than from your computer. This means that you can access your information from virtually anywhere.  Embrace the cloud to become agile and connected, whilst being confident of compliance with IG and data security.
Save us money
Save us money¬

Reduce storage costs by 60% to 80%, versus traditional storage methods using StorSimple, an on-premises tiered storage appliance that delivers high performance storage, live archiving and cloud data protection.
How can the cloud benefit our patients?
Patient benefit

The cloud opens up a world of opportunities to benefit the patient.  With wearable devices allowing patients to own, track and manage their care plans, the cloud provides the connecting engine for mobile monitoring from anywhere.
Data security and IG
Data security and IG

Azure has received OFFICIAL accreditation from the UK Government Pan Government Accreditor covering NHS trusts who hold or transact public sector data for business conducted at the OFFICIAL level of Security Classification. Details of the OFFICIAL accreditation can be found here and form part of the UK Government’s Cloud Security Principles.
How can the cloud benefit our clinicians?
Clinician benefit

Clinicians need to be able to access data from virtually anywhere, from any device. Cloud based technologies enable this to happen.  It also makes connecting and working with peers across the world easy, see how our technology has helped Operation Smile.
